reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Relatively easy to install, supports computer great
reviews.reviewText: Mounted my desktop under an electric standing desk using this stand. It was pretty easy to install, only hiccup is the weight and making sure you've got enough pressure when you first install into the underside of the desk. Once installed it's held my computer well, feels very secure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Free up desk space, great for my 8.5" wide PC
reviews.reviewText: I was looking to free up some desk space, and this fit my needs perfectly. I had to move the frame legs in a bit to fit the case, but that is due to the width of the case, no the PC Mount. I used thicker / longer screws for piece of mind (1 1/4" screws). All said and done, I am happy with the purchase and it give me more space on my deskop.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for large PC's, be warry of weight though
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my standing desk I was assembling, thinking that it would be good to get my PC off of the ground. It was slightly difficult to install, having no easy way to line up/predrill the holes into my desk.It supports the computer tower by using 2 springs and 2 locking friction arms, which means that it struggles with the weight of my PC, slowly lowering it even though my PC is below the maximum weight of 33 lbs. Additionally, due to it not being able to support the weight, the small plastic piece on the bottom of the computer bends out, leaving my computer leaning in the holder. I solved the problem by wrapping paracord around my PC and the device to lock it into place.It also doesn't hold my computer completely securely as my computer doesn't have a fully flat top, leaving my computer susceptible to slightly rocking back and forth. If they provided an arm on the top, the same as on the bottom, I would feel less worried about my computer tipping out.Finally, if you have a tower with top mounted power buttons, USB ports, etc. It it almost impossible to use them as the arm doesn't space the tower low enough. Pros:-Good for larger (lighter) computer towers-Good PriceCons:-Does not support 33 lbs as it suggests.-Somewhat difficult to install-Flimsy lower arm-Doesn't work well for PC's with top buttonsOverall, this device is a good device, and I've had it mounted under my standing desk for about 2 months. If you have a bulkier/heavier/non-flat-topped tower, make sure you take that into consideration before buying this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice "git yer PC off the floor" system.
reviews.reviewText: I was going to build custom boxes for two lab PCs until I saw these. I took a chance and have been very pleased with how they have worked out. I have a custom 6 foot table/desk I made recently and did not want my PCs sitting on the floor pulling in all the junk and dust that is unavoidable in any clean home. I mounted these under each end under the desk and fitted a large XPS PC in one side and a newer Optiplex 7000 in the other side. These PC mounts adjust in size to hold each and also makes dealing with rear cable management a breeze. I would definitely consider these for my next PC project.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I was very hesitant to buy at first I spent a while on intensive research but VIVO doesn’t disappoint (so far of course) it was very easy to build and it’s holding my Rosewill Prism mid tower. It works for other tables as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not very sturdy. Wouldn't recommend.
reviews.reviewText: I got this to mount my computer under my sit/stand desk a couple of months ago, and finally got around to putting it together under the desk. When I got my computer in it - The computer was too heavy for it, and it just bent the unit.I tried all sorts of things to make it work, but in the end it's just a piece of trash. I suppose if you've got some sort of mini PC or a special build that's ultra-light... It might work for you.Only reason it gets two stars is because it's relatively cheap. If it were much more expensive I'd probably give it one. Like... 5 bucks more and it'd be a one star review.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I am probably the only reviewer that is not sponsored. But I am telling you. This under the desk PC mount does it's job for large and heavy PC.I have an almost 35lbs Desktop with MSi 110R full ATX 3080Ti. I have a 14cm thick hardwood desk so I had my husband installed it for me. Luckily the screws didn't come out on top.Yeah, it is slightly wobbly so I put a padding on top. Still does its job!

reviews.reviewTitle: Garbage, cheap, will definitely fall and break ur pc and desk
reviews.reviewText: It is so cheaply made with really flimsy metal, as soon as I drilled it in it was very wobbly. I thought maybe it just needed the weight of my pc? Nope as soon as I put my pc on it, it started getting worse and was bending to the right. My pc weighs 28 lb and it can't handle it at all, false advertising.Unfortunately, I can't return this faulty product as I went over the one month return policy as I haven't had the time to set it up.Do not buy this unless you don't care about what could happen to your pc. A single small push and your pc will fall backwards as it has no support other than the plastic part on the right side of it.
I bought this item as it was supposed to be “heavy duty.” However it can’t support my normal size PC. After install my pc leans at an angle and looks like it might break off. Terrible product
